From e3ee4d39f6a6a83434bb1f7090de33e619727bab Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shubhrajyoti Datta <shubhraj@xilinx.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2015 20:48:15 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 180/827] i2c: xiic: Remove busy loop while waiting for bus busy

This patch comes from:
  https://github.com/Xilinx/linux-xlnx.git

Remove the busy loop  while waiting for bus busy.
Instead let the processor sleep.

Signed-off-by: Shubhrajyoti Datta <shubhraj@xilinx.com>
Signed-off-by: Wolfram Sang <wsa@the-dreams.de>
(cherry picked from commit b33aa252785eb6de2f5325a3338fa917a9b4bc66)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-xiic.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-xiic.c b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-xiic.c
index 5d133d4..41da902 100644
--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-xiic.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-xiic.c
@@ -524,7 +524,7 @@ static int xiic_busy(struct xiic_i2c *i2c)
 	 */
 	err = xiic_bus_busy(i2c);
 	while (err && tries--) {
-		mdelay(1);
+		msleep(1);
 		err = xiic_bus_busy(i2c);
 	}
 
